    <mj-section css-class="light-wrap" padding-bottom="20px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text>Dear Students, Faculty, and Staff:</mj-text>
        <mj-text>Earlier today, the Trump administration and the federal Office of Management and Budget (OMB) rescinded a directive to pause federal grants, aid, and other forms of assistance. With the rescission, all federal grant and loan funding will continue without disruption.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>The University recognizes that the initial directive caused concern and uncertainty, particularly for our students and faculty who rely on federal funding for their education and to conduct research. The advocacy and swift legal action taken by the California State University, the California Attorney General, and state and national partners in challenging the directive is greatly appreciated.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>The University remains committed to supporting our students and will continue working closely with the CSU Chancellorâ€™s Office to navigate any future changes affecting federal funding.</mj-text>

